svg.metadata: Created by FontForge 20141024 at Wed Sep 23 14:58:08 2015 By Jimmy Warting This typeface was designed for the International Typeface Corporation in 1990 by Eric Spiekermann and Just van Rossum. Designed as a stepping stone from typewriter type to traditional typographic design. The robust letter construction and even character widths make this face ideal for office correspondence. Legible at small sizes, it also withstands distortion on low resolution printers, photocopying and telefaxing. Additional styles and small caps were developed in 1998 by Ole Schaefer. Cyrillic version was developed at ParaType (ParaGraph) in 1994 by Tagir Safayev. Additional Cyrillic styles and small caps were developed for ParaType in 2003 by Isabella Chaeva.
